{
  "texts": [
    "The final essay score is determined by combining the scores derived from token-level and document-level representations with the score from segment-level representation.",
    "While the segment-level representation of essays prevents the truncation of essay sections, representing essay segments solely as token sequences lacks the concept of document structure.",
    "Augmenting BERT with essay-level features: Uto et al. (2020) proposed a hybrid approach that integrates essay-level features with BERT.",
    "This work incorporates various essay-level features, including length-based, syntactic, word-based, readability, semantic, argumentation, and prompt relevance features.",
    "These features are concatenated with BERT representation of the essay and passed through a fully connected linear layer as it is shown in Fig. 9."
  ]
}